"Don" == Don Blaheta <blahedo@quincy.edu> writes:

Don> PROTO-Proposal DB9 (Vanyel) Randomness (Creates a rule)

Don> All occurrences of the word "random" or forms of it shall be
Don> taken to mean "any of the choices with equally distributed
Don> possibility for each".

Don> ***End Proto

Don> That should take care of a few ambiguities.

and create a few: "any" can mean more than one.

how about:

      Whenever the Rules call for a "random" selection of a member
      from a set, the selection shall be made by uniquely indexing
      each member of the set, selecting a uniformly distributed
      discrete random value whose range is set of indices thus
      assigned, and then selecting the member of the set corresponding
      to the selected index.

k.
